## Writing Posts

### Frontmatter

Every post starts with TOML frontmatter:

```markdown
+++
layout = "post"
title = "Your Post Title"
date = "2024-01-14"
author = "Your Name"
tags = ["tutorial", "velt"]
+++

Your post content starts here...
```

### Frontmatter Fields

| Field | Required | Description | Example |
|-------|----------|-------------|---------|
| `layout` | ✅ | Always use `"post"` | `"post"` |
| `title` | ✅ | Post title | `"My First Post"` |
| `date` | ✅ | Publish date | `"2024-01-14"` |
| `author` | ❌ | Author name | `"John Doe"` |
| `tags` | ❌ | Post tags | `["tutorial"]` |
| `draft` | ❌ | Hide from listing | `true` |

<Callout type_="info">
Posts with `draft = true` won't appear in your blog listing but are still accessible via direct URL.
</Callout>

